You are working on HRTech, a Django 5 SaaS recruiting platform with multi-tenancy.
The codebase is production-bound. Prioritize correctness, security, and maintainability over brevity.

---

## Stack

- Python 3.10, Django 5, Gunicorn
- PostgreSQL 15 (primary database)
- Neo4j AuraDB (skills knowledge graph)
- Redis (Celery broker + cache)
- Celery 5 + Celery Beat (async tasks)
- OpenAI API / gpt-4o-mini (CV parsing)
- AWS S3 (CV storage via presigned URLs)
- django-allauth (authentication)
- Django REST Framework (API — in progress)
- Deployed on Render (web + worker + beat processes)

---

## Architecture

### Service layer (mandatory)
- Business logic lives exclusively in `core/services/`
- Views are HTTP-only: validate input, call service, return response
- Never put ORM queries or Neo4j queries directly in views
- Never put business logic in models (properties for simple derived values are ok)

### Multi-tenancy (active implementation)
- Every model has `organization = ForeignKey(Organization, ...)`
- Every ORM query MUST filter by `request.tenant` (injected by TenantMiddleware)
- Every Neo4j query MUST include `tenant: $tenant_id` parameter
- Use `Organization.neo4j_tenant_prefix` to build the tenant param value
- Never return cross-tenant data under any circumstance

### Dual persistence
- PostgreSQL: transactional data (Candidato, Vaga, AuditoriaMatch, etc.)
- Neo4j: skills graph (Habilidade, Area, SIMILAR_A, TEM_HABILIDADE)
- UUID is the sync key between both databases
- Write to PostgreSQL first, then Neo4j — never the reverse

---

