## Mandatory rules — never violate these

### Security
- NEVER hardcode credentials, tokens, secrets, or API keys
- ALWAYS use `python-decouple`: `config('VAR_NAME')`
- NEVER log PII: email, CPF, RG, CV content, phone numbers
- ALWAYS validate and sanitize user input before any operation
- ALWAYS use `get_or_create` instead of `exists() + get()` (race condition safety)
- ALWAYS use `@csrf_protect` on POST views that are not API endpoints
- NEVER expose stack traces in production (DEBUG=False handles this)

### Multi-tenancy
- EVERY new model needs `organization = ForeignKey(Organization, on_delete=models.CASCADE)`
- EVERY ORM queryset must be scoped: `.filter(organization=request.tenant)`
- EVERY Neo4j query must include `{tenant: $tenant_id}` in all MATCH clauses
- NEVER query without tenant scope, even in management commands

### LGPD compliance
- CVs are stored in S3 (private bucket) — access only via presigned URLs (15min TTL)
- Strip PII from CV text before sending to OpenAI: use `limpar_dados_pessoais()`
- AuditoriaMatch uses SET_NULL on candidato/vaga FKs intentionally — preserve audit trail
- Never log CV content, candidate email, or personal data at any log level

### Code patterns
- New business logic → new or existing service in `core/services/`
- New Celery task → `core/tasks.py`, use `@shared_task(bind=True, acks_late=True)`
- New model → needs migration, admin registration, and __str__ method
- New view → needs `@login_required` + role decorator + `@require_GET/POST`
- Every new feature needs a corresponding test in `core/tests/`

### Django ORM
- Use `select_related` and `prefetch_related` — never allow N+1 queries
- Use `update_fields=[...]` on `.save()` when updating specific fields only
- Use `bulk_create` and `bulk_update` for batch operations
- Cache expensive aggregations: `cache.get/set` with short TTL (60s for dashboard stats)
- Use `transaction.atomic()` for multi-step writes

### Neo4j
- Use `MERGE` not `CREATE` to avoid duplicate nodes
- Always parameterize queries — never f-string values into Cypher
- Use `run_query()` for reads, `run_write_query()` for writes
- Connection is a singleton — do not instantiate the driver directly
- Log errors with `logger.exception()` and re-raise — never swallow Neo4j errors silently

---

## Matching algorithm — handle with care

`core/matching.py` implements a 3-layer algorithm:
- Layer 1 (60%): direct skill match with temporal decay (0.85^years_inactive)
- Layer 2 (25%): similarity match via Neo4j SIMILAR_A relationships
- Layer 3 (15%): profile compatibility (area + seniority)

Do NOT refactor this file unless explicitly instructed.
Do NOT change weights (PESO_CAMADA_*) without explicit instruction.
Do NOT change FATOR_DECAIMENTO without explicit instruction.
Current version: VERSAO_ALGORITMO = "2.0.0"

---

## Testing

- Mock ALL external dependencies: Neo4j, OpenAI, S3, Celery
- Use `@patch('core.tasks.run_write_query')` pattern for Neo4j writes
- Use `@patch('core.tasks.get_openai_client')` for OpenAI calls
- Use `TransactionTestCase` when testing Celery tasks with `.apply()`
- Tests run with `--settings=hrtech.settings_test`
- Target: migrate settings_test from SQLite to PostgreSQL Docker
- Never use `distinct('field')` — works in PG but breaks SQLite test runner

---

## CV processing pipeline

Upload → RECEBIDO → PROCESSANDO (pdfplumber/OCR) → EXTRAINDO (OpenAI) → CONCLUIDO/ERRO

- Pipeline runs entirely in Celery worker (queue: openai)
- Status polling via HTMX every 3s using signed token (X-Status-Token header)
- Ghost job cleanup: `varrer_jobs_fantasmas` beat task runs hourly
- Rate limit: 20 OpenAI calls/min (configured in celery.py)
- MOCK_MODE: set OPENAI_MOCK_MODE=True in .env to skip OpenAI calls in dev

---

## API conventions (DRF — in progress)

- Authentication: JWT per tenant
- All endpoints scoped by tenant from token
- Rate limiting: per API key, not per IP
- Versioning: /api/v1/
- Response format: `{success: bool, data: ..., error: str | null}`

---

## Kanban pipeline mapping

Frontend columns → real EtapaProcesso values:
- `novo`       → TRIAGEM
- `em_analise` → ENTREVISTA_RH, TESTE_TECNICO, ENTREVISTA_TECNICA, PROPOSTA
- `aprovado`   → CONTRATADO
- `reprovado`  → REJEITADO, DESISTIU

Always use `PipelineService.KANBAN_TO_ETAPA` and `ETAPA_TO_KANBAN` for mapping.
Never hardcode column names in views or templates.

---

## What NOT to generate automatically

- Django migrations — always run `makemigrations` manually after model review
- Neo4j schema changes — coordinate with existing graph structure
- Changes to `core/matching.py` weights or algorithm structure
- Changes to `AuditoriaMatch` model (LGPD audit trail — immutable by design)
- Stripe webhook handlers — require explicit security review
- Any code that bypasses tenant scoping

